  "prompt": "What do I need to move to another country?",
  "response": "To move to another country, you'll generally need:\n\n1. Legal Requirements:\n- Valid passport\n- Visa or residence permit\n- Work permit (if planning to work)\n\n2. Financial Preparations:\n- Sufficient savings\n- Bank account in new country\n- Employment or income source\n- Health insurance\n- Emergency funds\n\n3. Documentation:\n- Birth certificate\n- Academic certificates\n- Professional qualifications\n- Marriage/divorce certificates\n- Criminal background check\n- Medical records\n\n4. Practical Preparations:\n- Housing arrangements\n- Language skills\n- Understanding of local culture\n- Job prospects\n- Transportation plans\n\n5. Personal Items:\n- Important personal documents\n- Clothing suitable for new climate\n- Necessary personal belongings\n- Medications\n\n6. Additional Considerations:\n- Tax obligations\n- Social security transfer\n- International moving services\n- Shipping personal items\n- Potential vaccination requirements\n\n7. Immigration Steps:\n- Research immigration laws\n- Contact embassy/consulate\n- Complete application processes\n- Attend interviews if required\n\n8. Personal Logistics:\n- Notify current employer\n- Cancel local subscriptions\n- Arrange mail forwarding\n- Close/transfer bank accounts\n\nSpecific requirements vary by country, so research the specific destination's regulations.",
